Description: bioZhena provides a cervix-monitoring diagnostic tool to monitor menstrual cycle vital sign data for use by doctor.
Full Description: Bringing women's personal management of sex life ("can I get pregnant today?") into the Information Age - and providing diagnostic menstrual vital-sign signatures to doctors & payers along the way.  The Ovulona™ from bioZhena is a women's healthcare breakthrough. The Menstrual Cycle is a Vital Sign® (promoted by NIH, DHHS, ACOG) and bioZhena’s information-rich menstrual cycle signature helps the user to either conceive or to avoid pregnancy naturally, without chemicals, hormones or surgery. The Ovulona home-use sensor generates "EKG-like" vital sign signatures (says an OBGYN doctor), a longitudinal recording for physicians and for healthcare payers. Like blood pressure and heart rate, a woman’s menstrual cycle is a vital sign of her overall health. The bioZhena technology has the potential to change the way how women and their physicians manage reproductive and general health, not just conception and contraception. See my PPS presentation (11 mostly narrated slides): Transforming Female Reproductive Health Management at https://biozhena.files.wordpress.com/2019/09/transforming-female-reproductive-health-management-918-1-ed-919-blue11slides-w.yellowref.to20sl.ppsx
